cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.CC, cs.DS

The paper deals with the non-computability of bar recursion operators in a programming language, which suggests that it belongs to the Logic (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Theory of Computation (cs.TL) categories. The use of nested sequential procedures and the non-definability of bar recursion in various models also suggest that it could belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories.
